 Here is a JavaScript function that takes an array of 5 numbers as input and checks if any of the numbers are prime. If a prime number is found, it will be printed to the console.

```javascript
function checkPrimes(numbers) {
    if (numbers.length !== 5) {
        console.error("Array must contain exactly 5 numbers.");
        return;
    }

    numbers.forEach(number => {
        if (isPrime(number)) {
            console.log(number);
        }
    });
}

function isPrime(num) {
    if (num <= 1) return false;
    if (num <= 3) return true;

    for (let i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(num); i++) {
        if (num % i === 0) {
            return false;
        }
    }

    return true;
}

// Example usage:
checkPrimes([4, 5, 15, 22, 29]);
```

This code includes two functions:

- `checkPrimes`: This function takes an array of numbers and checks if any of them are prime.
- `isPrime`: This function checks if a given number is prime.

